OL,3,C'Extraordinary' increase in abuse
OL,4,Caimed at GP staff, top medic warns
OL,6,FOne of England's leading medics has
OL,7,Fwarned of an "extraordinary" increase
OL,8,Fin abuse aimed at GP teams, which is
OL,9,Fpushing some family doctors to leave
OL,10,Fthe profession.
OL,12,FDr Claire Fuller, primary care medical
OL,13,Fdirector for NHS England, said it is
OL,14,Fnot acceptable to "bash" GPs, who are
OL,15,F"exhausted" and working "flat out",
OL,16,Fclaiming there has been a rise in
OL,17,Fattacks both physical and verbal.
