OL,3,C'Extraordinary' increase in abuse
OL,4,Caimed at GP staff, top medic warns
OL,6,F"When you talk to GPs about why they
OL,7,Fleave, they say one is about the
OL,8,Fworkload and the other one is about
OL,9,Frespect," she said.
OL,11,F"It has now become acceptable to bash
OL,12,FGPs, and that's not OK. I'm hearing
OL,13,Fthat from every GP I speak to. And
OL,14,Fpeople do leave because they've just
OL,15,Fhad enough.
OL,17,FDr Fuller added: "So if you think
OL,18,Fabout practice managers, every day,
OL,19,F(they) will get a phone call from a
OL,20,Fpatient that says, 'If I die today,
OL,21,Fit'll be your fault'.
