OL,3,C'Extraordinary' increase in abuse
OL,4,Caimed at GP staff, top medic warns
OL,6,F"And these are people that are working
OL,7,Fpart-time, on low incomes, that are
OL,8,Freceiving this level of abuse from the
OL,9,Fpublic."
OL,11,FThe comments come after a poll found
OL,12,Fmore than 80% of GP teams in the UK
OL,13,Fhave been verbally attacked by
OL,14,Fpatients.
OL,16,FThe Medical and Dental Defence Union
OL,17,Fof Scotland (MDDUS) surveyed 1,855
OL,18,Fdoctors in October 2024, with 690 GPs
OL,19,Fresponding. Of the family doctors that
OL,20,Ftook part, some 84% said their team
OL,21,Fhad suffered verbal abuse.
