OL,3,C'Extraordinary' increase in abuse
OL,4,Caimed at GP staff, top medic warns
OL,6,FChief medical officer at the MDDUS, Dr
OL,7,FJohn Holden, said violence and abuse
OL,8,Fcan have a "devastating impact" on NHS
OL,9,Fstaff already under "systemic
OL,10,Fpressure", with many having to take
OL,11,Ftime off sick or leaving the
OL,12,Fprofession completely.
OL,14,FAppearing at a consultation event for
OL,15,Fthe upcoming 10 Year Health Plan in
OL,16,FLiverpool, Dr Fuller also spoke of "a
OL,17,Fconstant narrative that GPs are not
OL,18,Fdoing what they should be" in the
OL,19,Fmedia, but said "the evidence we're
OL,20,Fgetting is the experience is improving.
