OL,3,C'Extraordinary' increase in abuse
OL,4,Caimed at GP staff, top medic warns
OL,6,F"It does matter when you keep reading
OL,7,Fin the press what a terrible job
OL,8,Fyou're doing when you're exhausted and
OL,9,Fyou've worked flat out and you haven't
OL,10,Fhad any lunch ` people are working
OL,11,Freally hard, and something has
OL,12,Fhappened that has changed in that
OL,13,Fnarrative."
OL,15,F"There's variation, but actually we're
OL,16,Fstarting to see improvement around the
OL,17,Fcountry," she added. "Not only have we
OL,18,Fgot more GPs, fewer GPs leaving, but
OL,19,Fwe are also starting to see that
OL,20,Fpatients' experience of access is
OL,21,Fstarting to improve.
